      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "### Example 14.3: From region to reversed integral\n",
        "\n",
        "Rewrite the integral\n",
        "\n",
        "$$\n",
        "\\int_0^4\\int_{y/2}^{\\sqrt{y+1}} f(x,y)\\,dx\\,dy\n",
        "$$\n",
        "\n",
        "with the order $dy\\,dx$.\n",
        "\n",
        "The given limits describe\n",
        "\n",
        "$$\n",
        "0\\le y\\le 4,\n",
        "\\qquad\n",
        "\\frac{y}{2}\\le x\\le \\sqrt{y+1}.\n",
        "$$\n",
        "\n",
        "Convert each boundary to $y$ as a function of $x$:\n",
        "\n",
        "$$\n",
        "x=\\frac{y}{2}\\quad \\Longleftrightarrow \\quad y=2x,\n",
        "$$\n",
        "\n",
        "and\n",
        "\n",
        "$$\n",
        "x=\\sqrt{y+1}\\quad \\Longleftrightarrow \\quad y=x^2-1.\n",
        "$$\n",
        "\n",
        "The region is between $y=x^2-1$ and $y=2x$, with $0\\le y\\le 4$. The horizontal band restriction causes the region to split when vertical slices change their lower boundary. We find the relevant $x$-range from the endpoints:\n",
        "\n",
        "- at $y=0$, $x$ ranges from $0$ to $1$;\n",
        "- at $y=4$, $x$ ranges from $2$ to $\\sqrt{5}$.\n",
        "\n",
        "A careful sketch shows\n",
        "\n",
        "$$\n",
        "\\int_0^4\\int_{y/2}^{\\sqrt{y+1}} f(x,y)\\,dx\\,dy\n",
        "=\n",
        "\\int_0^1\\int_0^{2x} f(x,y)\\,dy\\,dx\n",
        "+\n",
        "\\int_1^2\\int_{x^2-1}^{2x} f(x,y)\\,dy\\,dx\n",
        "+\n",
        "\\int_2^{\\sqrt{5}}\\int_{x^2-1}^{4} f(x,y)\\,dy\\,dx.\n",
        "$$\n",
        "\n",
        "This example illustrates why reversing order can require splitting. The geometry decides whether one integral is enough.\n",
        "\n",
        "## 14.6 Area of a plane region\n",
        "\n",
        "The area of a plane region $D$ can be computed by integrating the constant function $1$:\n",
        "\n",
        "::: {.callout-important}\n",
        "## Area by double integral\n",
        "\n",
        "$$\n",
        "\\operatorname{Area}(D)=\\iint_D 1\\,dA.\n",
        "$$\n",
        ":::\n",
        "\n",
        "For a Type I region,\n",
        "\n",
        "$$\n",
        "\\operatorname{Area}(D)\n",
        "=\n",
        "\\int_a^b\\int_{p(x)}^{q(x)}1\\,dy\\,dx\n",
        "=\n",
        "\\int_a^b(q(x)-p(x))\\,dx.\n",
        "$$\n",
        "\n",
        "For a Type II region,\n",
        "\n",
        "$$\n",
        "\\operatorname{Area}(D)\n",
        "=\n",
        "\\int_c^d\\int_{g(y)}^{h(y)}1\\,dx\\,dy\n",
        "=\n",
        "\\int_c^d(h(y)-g(y))\\,dy.\n",
        "$$\n",
        "\n",
        "### Example 14.4: Area between a line and a parabola\n",
        "\n",
        "Find the area of the region bounded by\n",
        "\n",
        "$$\n",
        "y=x-1\n",
        "\\qquad \\text{and} \\qquad\n",
        " y^2=2x+6.\n",
        "$$\n",
        "\n",
        "Write both curves as $x$ in terms of $y$:\n",
        "\n",
        "$$\n",
        "y=x-1 \\quad \\Longleftrightarrow \\quad x=y+1,\n",
        "$$\n",
        "\n",
        "and\n",
        "\n",
        "$$\n",
        "y^2=2x+6 \\quad \\Longleftrightarrow \\quad x=\\frac{y^2-6}{2}.\n",
        "$$\n",
        "\n",
        "Find intersections by substituting $x=y+1$ into $y^2=2x+6$:\n",
        "\n",
        "$$\n",
        "y^2=2(y+1)+6,\n",
        "\\qquad\n",
        " y^2-2y-8=0,\n",
        "\\qquad\n",
        "(y-4)(y+2)=0.\n",
        "$$\n",
        "\n",
        "Thus $-2\\le y\\le 4$. The parabola lies on the left and the line lies on the right, so\n",
        "\n",
        "$$\n",
        "\\begin{aligned}\n",
        "\\operatorname{Area}(D)\n",
        "&=\n",
        "\\int_{-2}^{4}\\int_{(y^2-6)/2}^{y+1} 1\\,dx\\,dy \\\\\n",
        "&=\n",
        "\\int_{-2}^{4}\\left(y+1-\\frac{y^2-6}{2}\\right)\\,dy \\\\\n",
        "&=\n",
        "\\int_{-2}^{4}\\left(y+4-\\frac{y^2}{2}\\right)\\,dy \\\\\n",
        "&=18.\n",
        "\\end{aligned}\n",
        "$$"
      ],
      "id": "70f72069"
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {
        "fig-width": 6.5
      },
