        "## 14.7 Splitting regions\n",
        "\n",
        "Not every region is Type I or Type II in a single piece. Some regions must be split into simpler pieces.\n",
        "\n",
        "Suppose\n",
        "\n",
        "$$\n",
        "D=D_1\\cup D_2\n",
        "$$\n",
        "\n",
        "where the interiors of $D_1$ and $D_2$ do not overlap. Then\n",
        "\n",
        "$$\n",
        "\\iint_D f(x,y)\\,dA\n",
        "=\n",
        "\\iint_{D_1} f(x,y)\\,dA\n",
        "+\n",
        "\\iint_{D_2} f(x,y)\\,dA.\n",
        "$$\n",
        "\n",
        "This is the two-dimensional version of splitting a one-variable integral at a point."
      ],
      "id": "e1adeef6"
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {
        "fig-width": 6.5
      },
      "source": [
        "#| label: fig-ch14-splitting-region\n",
        "#| fig-cap: Some regions are best handled by splitting them into simpler Type I or Type II pieces.\n",
        "import numpy as np\n",
        "import matplotlib.pyplot as plt\n",
        "\n",
        "x1 = np.linspace(-1, 0, 200)\n",
        "x2 = np.linspace(0, 1, 200)\n",
        "upper1 = 1 - x1**2\n",
        "upper2 = 1 - x2**2\n",
        "lower1 = -0.2 + 0*x1\n",
        "lower2 = x2 - 0.2\n",
        "\n",
        "fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(6.5, 5))\n",
        "ax.fill_between(x1, lower1, upper1, alpha=0.3, label='$D_1$')\n",
        "ax.fill_between(x2, lower2, upper2, alpha=0.3, label='$D_2$')\n",
        "ax.plot(np.r_[x1, x2], 1 - np.r_[x1, x2]**2, color='black', label='upper boundary')\n",
        "ax.plot(x1, lower1, color='black')\n",
        "ax.plot(x2, lower2, color='black')\n",
        "ax.axvline(0, linestyle='--', linewidth=1)\n",
        "ax.set_xlabel('$x$')\n",
        "ax.set_ylabel('$y$')\n",
        "ax.set_title('A region split into two pieces')\n",
        "ax.grid(True, alpha=0.25)\n",
        "ax.legend()\n",
        "plt.show()"
      ],
