      "source": [
        "::: {.callout-note}\n",
        "## When splitting is necessary\n",
        "\n",
        "Splitting is needed when a single vertical or horizontal slice does not enter and exit the region through the same pair of boundary curves for the whole range. Splitting is not a failure; it is part of correct geometric modeling.\n",
        ":::\n",
        "\n",
        "## 14.8 Volume under a surface over a curved base\n",
        "\n",
        "If $f(x,y)\\ge 0$ on a region $D$, then\n",
        "\n",
        "$$\n",
        "V=\\iint_D f(x,y)\\,dA\n",
        "$$\n",
        "\n",
        "is the volume of the solid above $D$ and below the surface $z=f(x,y)$.\n",
        "\n",
        "### Example 14.5: Volume over a triangular region\n",
        "\n",
        "Let $D$ be the triangular region with vertices $(0,0)$, $(1,0)$, and $(1,2)$. Find the volume under\n",
        "\n",
        "$$\n",
        "z=3+x+y\n",
        "$$\n",
        "\n",
        "over $D$.\n",
        "\n",
        "The region is\n",
        "\n",
        "$$\n",
        "D=\\{(x,y):0\\le x\\le 1,\\ 0\\le y\\le 2x\\}.\n",
        "$$\n",
        "\n",
        "Therefore\n",
        "\n",
        "$$\n",
        "\\begin{aligned}\n",
        "V\n",
        "&=\\int_0^1\\int_0^{2x}(3+x+y)\\,dy\\,dx \\\\\n",
        "&=\\int_0^1\\left[(3+x)y+\\frac{y^2}{2}\\right]_0^{2x}\\,dx \\\\\n",
        "&=\\int_0^1\\left(6x+2x^2+2x^2\\right)\\,dx \\\\\n",
        "&=\\int_0^1(6x+4x^2)\\,dx \\\\\n",
        "&=3+\\frac{4}{3}\n",
        "=\n",
        "\\frac{13}{3}.\n",
        "\\end{aligned}\n",
        "$$"
      ],
      "id": "c4484a5d"
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {
        "fig-width": 7
      },
      "source": [
        "#| label: fig-ch14-volume-over-triangle\n",
        "#| fig-cap: A surface over a triangular base region. The double integral gives volume.\n",
        "import numpy as np\n",
        "import matplotlib.pyplot as plt\n",
        "from matplotlib.tri import Triangulation\n",
        "\n",
        "# Triangular grid: 0 <= x <= 1, 0 <= y <= 2x\n",
        "xs = []\n",
        "ys = []\n",
        "for x0 in np.linspace(0, 1, 35):\n",
        "    for y0 in np.linspace(0, 2*x0, max(2, int(35*x0)+2)):\n",
        "        xs.append(x0)\n",
        "        ys.append(y0)\n",
        "xs = np.array(xs)\n",
        "ys = np.array(ys)\n",
        "zs = 3 + xs + ys\n",
        "tri = Triangulation(xs, ys)\n",
        "\n",
        "fig = plt.figure(figsize=(7, 5))\n",
        "ax = fig.add_subplot(111, projection='3d')\n",
        "ax.plot_trisurf(tri, zs, alpha=0.75, linewidth=0.2)\n",
        "ax.set_xlabel('$x$')\n",
        "ax.set_ylabel('$y$')\n",
        "ax.set_zlabel('$z$')\n",
        "ax.set_title('Volume under $z=3+x+y$ over a triangle')\n",
        "plt.show()"
      ],
      "id": "fig-ch14-volume-over-triangle",
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
